[1] South Korea, 2 fatalities - media report
Date: 2 Jun 2015 [time zone variance]
Source: Yonhap [edited]
http://english.yonhapnews.co.kr/news/2015/06/02/0200000000AEN20150602000351315.html


South Korea reported the country's 1st 2 deaths from Middle East Respiratory Syndrome (MERS) on Tuesday [2 Jun 2015], saying a suspected patient was confirmed to have the virus after death and another confirmed patient also died.

The health ministry also reported 6 new cases of the viral disease, bringing the total to 25. The new cases included the country's 1st tertiary infections as 2 people were found to have contracted the virus from a secondarily infected patient.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Kunihiko Iizuka

[According to another media report, the 2 deaths involved a 58-year-old woman who had had contact with South Korea's 1st patient who died of acute respiratory failure on Monday [1 Jun 2015], and a 71-year-old man who had been on respiratory support with a history of kidney ailments also died on Monday [1 Jun 2015] (http://www.reuters.com/article/2015/06/01/us-health-mers-southkorea-idUSKBN0OH1P120150601). These are cases No: 6 and 25 in the Korean MOH line listing presented in section [2] below.

The HealthMap/ProMED map of South Korea can be found at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3402059,195. - Mod.MPP]

