[2] South Korea, total 25 cases - Korean MOH 2 Jun 2015, RFI
Date: 2 Jun 2015
Source: Korean Ministry of Health and Welfare [in Korean, machine trans. edited]
http://www.mw.go.kr/front_new/al/sal0301vw.jsp?PAR_MENU_ID=04&MENU_ID=0403&SEARCHKEY=&SEARCHVALUE=&page=1&CONT_SEQ=322742


An additional 6 [MERS] patients have been confirmed, bringing the total number of Korean cases to 25 including 2 deaths.

Of the 6 newly confirmed cases:
- 4 patients are secondary cases associated with spread in the 2nd hospital [hospital B] where the index case was admitted, involving medical patients or family members, all of whom had contact with the 1st patient (the index case). Two patients are from D hospital; both had contact with the 2nd patient diagnosed.

Of these 4 patients referred to above as secondary cases, all were at the hospital between 15 and 17 May 2015, either hospitalized or visiting a family member who was hospitalized in the same ward as the index case.

The other 2 patients were in the hospital from 28-30 May 2015 in the same ward as one of the secondary cases. [Hence, these 2 cases are referred to as tertiary cases.]

Listing of 25 cases:
Middle East Respiratory Syndrome (MERS)

