[4] Saudi Arabia, 2 new cases, 1 death - MOH 1 Jun 2015, RFI
Date: 1 Jun 2015
Source: Saudi MOH [edited]
http://www.moh.gov.sa/en/CCC/PressReleases/Pages/Statistics-2015-06-01-001.aspx


As of 12 Noon, today, 1 Jun 2015, there have been a total of:
1016 laboratory confirmed cases of MERS-CoV infection including
447 deaths,
562 recoveries, and
7 currently active cases.

In the past 24 hours, there have been a total of:
2 newly confirmed cases;
1 newly reported fatality.

Information on newly confirmed cases:
1- Hufoof: 54-year-old Saudi male, non-healthcare worker, currently admitted to the ICU in critical condition. Possible history of contact with other case(s) currently under review.

2- Hufoof: 50-year-old Saudi male, non-healthcare worker, currently in stable condition and admitted to the ward. Possible history of contact with other case(s) currently under review.

Information on newly reported fatality:
Huraymeila: 41-year-old Expat male, non-healthcare worker, history of pre-existing co-morbidities [reported by MOH as newly confirmed case on 4 May 2015, at which time was noted to be in critical condition. At time of initial report, there was a negative history of contact with other case(s) in either the healthcare environment or in the community.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[As of today, 1 Jun 2015 there have been a total of 1016 cases of MERS-CoV infection including 447 deaths (reported case fatality rate 44.0 percent) reported from Saudi Arabia since 2012. The outbreak in Hufoof is ongoing as cases continue to occur - there have now been 20 cases reported from Hufoof since 20 Apr 2015. One wonders what is facilitating the nosocomial spread in an area that has already had nosocomial transmission in the past. More information on the epidemiology of this outbreak would be greatly appreciated.

A map showing the location of Hufoof and of Huraymeila (the location of the fatal case) can be found at the source URL. - Mod.MPP]

